A Few Improvements I'd Make
There are three refinements I would make before implementation:
1. Replace role with project_role
In project_members, name the field project_role instead of role. This makes it clear that someone can have different roles in different projects (for example, Backend Engineer in one project and Project Manager in another).
2. Allow deliverables to attach to more than features
While most deliverables belong to features, some are tied to meetings (e.g., meeting minutes) or projects (e.g., architecture documents). Rather than creating multiple deliverable tables, use a flexible pattern:
related_type (Feature, Meeting, Project)
related_id
This keeps one deliverables table while allowing broader use.
3. Make feature status configurable
Instead of hardcoding statuses like Planning, Design, Development, and Testing, consider storing them in a small configuration (or enum managed centrally). That gives you flexibility to adjust the workflow later without changing the database structure.
